text.tspan: GUI Toolkit for Ubuntu Touch v04.1

flowRoot.flowPara: Remember that the important thing is to focus on the content. Maybe it's much better than before using this Toolkit think schematically how your app will work, interactivity, order, etc.. You should first design your app in paper or digital but always focusing on content. Try abstraerte all graphic element in your design before starting to include these elements in your design.
Use, enjoy, share.
When you have defined your design, use the Toolkit to find visual styles and make them consistent with design guidelines Ubuntu.
Remember

I present the GUI Toolkit v04 for all designers who want to easily design some proposals for Ubuntu Touch. It is easy, customizable and scalable (edited with Inkscape). This promotes reducing the distance between a designer and a developer. Enjoy it and share it. From the community for the community!
The Toolkit
